#20033
Temple of Sargonnas~
Upon entering this room a sharp chill washes over your body.  The pillars 
continue into this room, and come to meet along the far north wall.  The center 
piece of the temple is a massive fountain, with a statue of the God Sargonnas at its center.
His eyes glow bright red, he weilds a flaming scimitar in his hand.  The sound that you 
thought was running water, is in fact blood, flowing up around the base of the 
statue, and running into the fountain.  
Blood also oozes from the statues leering mouth.  Behind the blood fountain, set up 
on a dais is an ornate altar made out of black granite.  Lying upon the altar is 
what is left of a corpse, which has been dissembled and mutilated.
~
